OL,3,C'Simple' colour card for describing
OL,4,Cbodily fluids could improve patient
OL,5,Coutcomes
OL,7,FEach colour on the palette has a
OL,8,Funique "hex code" ` an international
OL,9,Fcode for colour identification ` that
OL,10,Fcan be entered into a patient's notes,
OL,11,Fwhich other clinicians can then use to
OL,12,Ffind the exact colour being referred
OL,13,Fto by the patient.
OL,15,FThe researchers said by reducing the
OL,16,Flevel of subjectivity when describing
OL,17,Fdifferent colours, the tool can help
OL,18,Fmake diagnosis faster and more
OL,19,Faccurate, and so help improve patient
OL,20,Foutcomes.
OL,26,@pD@HOUpD@QO]
