OL,3,C'Simple' colour card for describing
OL,4,Cbodily fluids could improve patient
OL,5,Coutcomes
OL,7,F"In our documentation we then write,
OL,8,F'the patient says it's greeny-brown or
OL,9,Fbluey-black', or whatever colour it's
OL,10,Fdescribed as, and the next person may
OL,11,Fhave another interpretation of that
OL,12,Fcolour in their head.
OL,14,F"This toolkit really standardises
OL,15,Fthat. It takes the subjectivity out of
OL,16,Fit and makes sure everyone's working
OL,17,Ffrom the same colour."
OL,19,FShe went on to describe the impact
OL,20,Fthis could have on patient outcomes.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@AOUyD@VO]
