OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F303A1767402403
OL,3,C'Simple' colour card for describing
OL,4,Cbodily fluids could improve patient
OL,5,Coutcomes
OL,7,F"But also we know of one nurse who's
OL,8,Fusing it with stroke patients who have
OL,9,Fsomething called aphasia, which means
OL,10,Fthey can see, they can understand,
OL,11,Fthey can think just fine, but getting
OL,12,Fwords out is really hard.
OL,14,F"But this means that for them, a
OL,15,Fconversation that would be a struggle
OL,16,Fbecomes much more seamless and much
OL,17,Fmore easy."
OL,19,FMr Yorkstone added that the
OL,20,F"simplicity" of the tool is key to its
OL,21,Feffectiveness.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@AOUyD@KO]|D@AOU|D@LO]
